  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposal constitutes development under the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, and the local planning authority is not satisfied that, based on the drawings submitted as part of the application, this proposal falls within any class of 'permitted development' specified within Schedule 2 to the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).\r\nINFORMATIVE: The proposed development fails to comply with Article 3, paragraph 9A(a) and 9A(b) as Schedule 2 does not authorise the development of dwellinghouses with a gross internal area of less than 37sqm and that do not meet the minimum space standards of the nationally described space standard issued by the Department for Communities and Local Government on 27th March 2015. \r\n\r\nThe proposed development also fails to comply with conditions G.1(a) and (b) of Class G of Part 1, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended) as (a) the retail unit building would be on the ground floor and the same floor as the parts of the building used as a flat and (b) the building has a display window at ground floor level and part of the ground floor would be used as a flat. \r\n\r\nThe proposed development fails to comply with Schedule 2, Part 3, Class G of The Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended) as the Local Planning Authority is not satisfied the proposal complies with the required use\r\n\r\n"
